	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />As a fan of Ruby, I would love to have something within the vein of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interactive_Ruby_Shell" class="postlink">IRB</a> to quickly test my code<br />so that I can rapidly learn the language.<br /><br />I've messed around with apple ii emulators and seen videos on youtube where you can quickly write<br />to memory and test your code.<br /><br />Oddly enough, I haven't found a modern assembler that works that way.  Obviously, I'm not running a<br />native 6502 environment like the C64 or Apple ii, but that doesn't mean much with modern virtual systems.<br /><br />Anyway, perhaps someone here has such a tool in their arsenal?  I suppose if enough time goes by,<br />I could write something myself, but I'm more focused on actual game making.<br /><br />Thanks.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
